cs.SD, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CE 

The paper proposes the use of recurrent neural networks (RNNs) for automated cardiac auscultation and detection of abnormal heartbeat detection. This involves processing sequential or temporal data, which is a common problem in the sub-categories of machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.SD (Sound), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are likely sub-categories. Additionally, the use of RNNs suggests a focus on neural networks, which is a common topic in the sub-categories of neural networks (cs.NE) and computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV). Finally, since the application is in the healthcare domain, cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is also a possible sub-category.
